# Copy this file to `.env.local` in this same directory (project root), then fill in values.
# `.env.local` is gitignored — never commit real secrets.
#
# Local dev: after editing `.env.local`, restart `pnpm dev`.
# Production (Vercel): Project → Settings → Environment Variables — add the same names there.

# Required — from https://resend.com/api-keys
RESEND_API_KEY=

# Optional — "From" address. The domain MUST be verified in Resend first:
# https://resend.com/domains — add DNS records, wait until status is verified.
#
# If you see "The domain is invalid", you either used an unverified domain here, or
# RESEND_FROM has a typo. Fix: verify the domain in Resend, or delete this line to use
# Resend’s built-in test sender: onboarding@resend.dev (OK for local / limited testing).
#
# Example after your domain is verified:
# RESEND_FROM="Portfolio <noreply@yourdomain.com>"
RESEND_FROM=

# Optional — where contact form messages are delivered. If unset, uses `email` from `content/contact.ts`.
# CONTACT_TO=hello@yansons.online

# --- Notes ---
#
# Public domains (gmail.com, google.com, yahoo.com, …) cannot be used as RESEND_FROM —
# Resend only sends from domains you own and verify (anti-spoofing). Your own site domain is fine.
#
# Use Resend’s sender only (no custom From):
# Leave RESEND_FROM empty. The app uses `onboarding@resend.dev`. Fine for testing; in production
# mail will show as from Resend’s domain, not yours — use a verified domain for a professional From.
#
# Custom mail From your Squarespace-registered domain:
# 1. In Resend: Domains → Add domain (e.g. yansons.online).
# 2. Resend shows DNS records (SPF, DKIM, …). In Squarespace: Settings → Domains → your domain
#    → DNS settings (or DNS if you use Squarespace nameservers) → add those records exactly.
# 3. Wait until Resend shows the domain as verified, then set e.g.
#    RESEND_FROM="Portfolio <noreply@yansons.online>"
#
# Receiving mail (hello@…) is separate: use Squarespace email, Google Workspace, Zoho, or a forwarder;
# set CONTACT_TO to that inbox. Resend only handles *sending* the contact form to you.
